Your idea is good 👍 but don’t say “I never got a chance to work in an MNC.”
That can sound a little negative or like you are joining only because it’s an MNC, not because of the company itself.

Instead, frame it in a positive and growth-focused way.

Better Answer Structure

Appreciation for the company

Your growth goals

How your experience fits

Example Answer (Good)

I’m looking for opportunities where I can work on large-scale systems and global products. From what I understand, Altimetrik works with enterprise clients and focuses on digital product engineering.
In such environments you deal with high-volume data, scalability challenges, and performance optimization, which are areas I’m very interested in.
With my 5+ years of Ruby on Rails experience, I feel this would be a great place to contribute while also learning how large-scale systems are designed and maintained.

Shorter Version (Also Good)

I’m interested in working on large-scale applications and enterprise-level systems. Companies like Altimetrik work with global clients where performance, scalability, and clean architecture become very important. With my experience in Ruby on Rails and backend development, I believe I can contribute well while also growing by solving more complex engineering problems.

Key Points You Want Them to Hear

You want large scale systems

You care about performance and scalability

You want to grow technically

Your Rails experience fits their work

❌ Avoid saying:

“I want to join because it’s an MNC.”

“I never got a chance before.”

✅ Pro tip for Hiring Manager round:
Sometimes they ask a follow-up:

“What do you know about Altimetrik?”

Just say 1–2 lines:

Altimetrik focuses on digital product engineering, data, and AI-driven solutions, and works with global enterprises to modernize their platforms.

